import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['distance'])
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Distance (miles)')
    ax.axhline(data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Count the number of flights per origin and destination airport
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()
    destination_counts = data['destination'].value_counts()
    total_counts = origin_counts.add(destination_counts, fill_value=0).sort_values(ascending=False)

    # Create the bar chart
    ax = total_counts.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 6), color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.title("Which airports have the highest number of flights?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Airport")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Flights")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    # Add a legend
    ax.legend(["Number of Flights"])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%m%d%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    flights_by_date = data['date'].value_counts().sort_index()
    
    plt.plot(flights_by_date.index, flights_by_date.values)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights by date?')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
